"title": "8777: lust",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8777: lust",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>An overpowering and compulsive desire or passion, especially of a sexual nature. Scripture condemns lust of all kinds, and urges believers to show self-control.</p>\n<h2>Lust has its origins in the heart and mind</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:25-Prov6:29\">PRO 6:25–6:29</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:28\">MAT 5:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen3:6\">GEN 3:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job31:1\">JOB 31:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:13-Jas1:15\">JAS 1:13–1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:16\">1JN 2:16</a></p>\n<h2>Lust is natural to unbelievers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:21-Rom1:27\">ROM 1:21–1:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:5\">ROM 7:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:9-1Cor6:10\">1CO 6:9–6:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:3\">1PE 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:14-2Pet2:18\">2PE 2:14–2:18</a></p>\n<h2>Believers can and must fight against lust by showing self-control</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16-Gal5:21\">GAL 5:16–5:21</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5\">COL 3:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor9:27\">1CO 9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:24\">GAL 5:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:22\">EPH 4:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:4-1Thess4:5\">1TH 4:4–4:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim2:22\">2TI 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:12\">TIT 2:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:11\">1PE 2:11</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of lust</h2>\n<h3>Lust expressed as sexual desire</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen39:6-Gen39:12\">GEN 39:6–39:12</a> <em>Potiphar's wife and Joseph</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:2-2Sam11:5\">2SA 11:2–11:5</a> <em>David and Bathsheba</em></p>\n<h3>Lust for money</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:9-1Tim6:10\">1TI 6:9–6:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:3\">1TI 3:3</a></p>\n<h3>The lustful desire of Israel and Judah for alliances</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek23:1-Ezek23:21\">EZK 23:1–23:21</a> <em>Both kingdoms sought security from such alliances, rather than trusting in God.</em></p>",
